Request approval to register









            Direct your query to the best people to handle it
          Heading link



 
Copy link



If you need MSCS department approval to take a 100/200/300/400 level course please file a request for department approval.  Even if you are a graduate student the Director of Undergraduate Studies grants approval for registering for these courses.


 

If you are an undergraduate (or prospective undergraduate) student, the Undergraduate Studies staff are most likely to be able to assist you with any issues you are having.
If you are a graduate (or prospective graduate) student, the Graduate Studies staff are most likely to be able to assist you with any issues you are having.
If you are in or interested in the various Teaching of Mathematics programs at UIC, please contact the Office of Math Education.
 
A full list of department staff and administrators is available as well.  If you cannot find the best person to direct your inquiry to try contacting the main office.





